title.rendered: IPL 2023 Playoffs Scenario – How Will The Teams Qualify For Final Four?

content.rendered:
The IPL 2023 has now started to reach its mid-stage which has always been a crucial one in all the previous seasons too. The game will now gain more intensity as the teams will now be entering the playoffs, as of now none of the teams has made a space in the playoffs. The teams are playing on the verge of either getting into the playoffs or getting out. The standing of all the teams is as follows for IPL 2023:

Gujarat Titans:

Achieving 16 points from 11 matches that they have played so far, Gujarat Titans sit at the top of the IPL 2023 teams table and might get into the playoffs for the second consecutive season. If GTs manage to win 1 match out of the remaining 3 they will make their way in the playoffs.

Chennai Super Kings:

CSK has 13 points from 11 matches, with 2 wins in the remaining 3 matches will ensure their entry into the playoffs but if they win just 1 game of the 3 they will have to be depended on the results of other teams as well for the playoffs.

Mumbai Indians:

Mumbai Indians have achieved the number 3 position in the team standings. If they win the 3 matches, they will secure their position in the playoffs if they won 2 then they will be depended on the results of other teams as well.

Lucknow Super Giants:

They have achieved 11 points from 11 matches, a confirmed entry into the playoffs would mean winning all 3 matches, anything less than that, they will have to depend on the result of other teams.

Rajasthan Royals:

The game is fairly simple for RR, 3 wins in the matches will mean they will continue in the tournament anything less & they will be out unless any 1 of the top 4 teams drops points.

Kolkata Knight Riders:

The situation is not much different from RR, KKR also has the same 10 points from 11 matches. And to qualify for playoffs they need to win all 3 matches. The next three matches are with RR, CSK & LSG & all of them are in the race for the top 4, a defeat would mean the end of the IPL 2023 journey for KKR.

Royal Challengers Bangalore:

Having 10 points from 11 matches & a net run-rate of -0.345 RCB stands at 7th place in the team standing table. They need to win the 3 matches & also hope that the other teams do not collect the crucial 16 points to qualify for the IPL 2023 playoffs.

Punjab Kings:

Apart from winning the three matches & gaining 16 points, they have to win the matches with large margins & also depend on the result of other teams as well.

Sunrisers Hyderabad:

They have 4 matches in hand & will have to win them all to gain an entry in the playoffs, but they are also depending on the results of the other teams as well.

Delhi Capitals:

Being at the bottom of the team’s standings they need to win all 4 matches & they are also depending on the standings of other teams as well to qualify for the playoffs.
